    <summary>This tool uses the difference in cell values of a center cell and its neighbours (as specified by the kernel) as features for a Principal Component Analysis (PCA). This method has been used by Thomas and Herzfeld (2004) to parameterize the topography for a subsequent regionalization of climate variables with the principal components as predictors in a regression model. </summary>
